Titolo: Illusion of Gaia

Anno: 1993

Descrizione: Illusion of Gaia, known in Europe and Australia as Illusion of Time, is an action role-playing game developed by Quintet for the Super Nintendo Entertainment System. The game was published by Enix (now Square-Enix) in Japan in 1993, and Nintendo published it in North America and PAL territories in 1994 and 1995 respectively. Set in a fantasy reimagining of Earth, the game's plot centers on a boy named Will who is chosen to save the world from an impending disaster. During the course of the game, the player guides Will through levels based on ancient ruins of real-world civilizations and Wonders of the World, such as the Great Pyramid and the Great Wall of China.

Genere: Action RPG

Valutazione: N/A
